title: Grateful Dead Live at Madison Square Garden on 1981-03-09
description:
Set 1

Feel Like A Stranger, Althea-> CC Rider, Ramble On Rose-> El Paso, Deep Elem Blues, Beat It On Down The Line, Bird Song, Minglewood Blues

Set 2

China Cat Sunflower-> I Know You Rider-> Samson & Delilah, Ship of Fools, Estimated Prophet-> Uncle John's Band-> Drums-> The Other One-> Stella Blue-> Good Lovin', E: U.S. Blues

reviews.review_text:
rolling thunder I actually never fully listened to this show, although I had it for a long time.  The audiences I had never did it justice and I'm glad I waited for the matrix.

they found 'the sound' in this one. 

Great tour overall, I have a couple of other favorites from spring 81

2-27-81  one of my favorite minglewoods
3-2-81   althea
5-4-81   a new copy just came into circulation
5-5-81    a melt down 

peace

Ps
was brent sniffing glue during minglewood?
a bad synth experience I guess.

YEEEEE HAW! It is good to stay away from the 'BEST' discusion, so I'm just going to say that this particular performance of the song 'China Cat Sunflower' into that 'I Know You Rider' song was a good one.
